Section 1:
1 L.D. 704
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 ENVIRONMENT AND NATURAL RESOURCES
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 443, L.D. 704, “An Act to Clarify
10 Performance Standards for Quarries”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 38 MRSA §490-X, as amended by PL 2007, c. 297, §8 and PL 2011, c. 682,
14 §38, is further amended by enacting at the end a new paragraph to read:
15 Notwithstanding any provision of this article to the contrary, a person exempt from the
16 requirements of this article that is operating a quarry one acre in size or less; that is
17 operating a quarry that has a total excavated area, including adjacent parcels under a
18 common owner or operator, that is one acre in size or less; or that is operating a quarry and
19 conducting an excavation or grading preliminary to a construction project shall comply
20 with the blasting notification requirements under section 490-Z, subsection 14, paragraph
21 O if the person intends to conduct blasting at that quarry or as part of that excavation or
22 grading.'
23 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
24 number to read consecutively.
25 SUMMARY
2266 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, replaces the bill and
2277 amends the quarrying law to provide that a person that is operating a quarry or operating a
2288 quarry and conducting an excavation or grading preliminary to a construction project and
2299 that is otherwise exempt from the requirements of that law that intends to conduct blasting
3300 at that quarry or as part of that excavation or grading is required to comply with certain
3311 quarrying law notification requirements for blasting.
32 Those notification requirements provide that, prior to blasting, the owner or operator
33 must develop and implement a plan that provides an opportunity for prior notification of a
34 planned blast for all persons located within 1,000 feet of the blast site. Notification may
Page 1 - 132LR2248(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 443, L.D. 704
315 be by telephone, in writing, by public notice in a newspaper of general circulation in the
326 area affected or by other means identified in the plan.
337 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
348 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR2248(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
